   <body>
      <ol>
         <li>
            <p>Remove the plate in the bottom left side of the power section
of the UPS cabinet.</p>
            <stepxmp>
               <fig>
                  <title>Front View of the UPS Cabinet</title>
                  <image href="../Images/100_kva__connect_battery_cables_from_adjacent_battery_cabinet_remove_cover_120mm_0000110610.svg"
                         scalefit="yes"
                         scope="local"
                         placement="inline"/>
               </fig>
            </stepxmp>
         </li>
         <li>
            <p>Note the position of the two busbars inside the power section
of the UPS cabinet and mark it on the left side panel.</p>
         </li>
         <li>
            <p>Note the position of the cable inlet in the power section
of the UPS cabinet and mark it on the left side panel.</p>
         </li>
         <li>
            <p>Remove the left side panel from the power section of the
UPS cabinet.</p>
            <stepxmp>
               <fig>
                  <title>Front View of the UPS Cabinet</title>
                  <image href="../Images/100_kva_remove_side_panel_120mm_0000110609.svg"
                         scalefit="yes"
                         scope="local"
                         placement="inline"/>
               </fig>
            </stepxmp>
         </li>
         <li>
            <p>Drill holes and install conduits for signal cables and
power cables in the side panel. Conduits are not provided.</p>
            <stepxmp>
               <hazardstatement type="danger">
                  <messagepanel>
                     <typeofhazard>Hazard of electric shock, explosion, or arc flash</typeofhazard>
                     <howtoavoid>Do not drill or cut holes for cables or conduits with
the side panel installed and do not drill or cut holes in close proximity
to the UPS.</howtoavoid>
                  </messagepanel>
               </hazardstatement>
               <fig>
                  <title>Front View of the UPS Cabinet</title>
                  <image href="../Images/Reality_pxc_nam_75-100_kva_adjacent_battery_cabinet_busbar_placement_120mm_0000134962.svg"
                         scalefit="yes"
                         placement="inline"/>
               </fig>
            </stepxmp>
         </li>
         <li>
            <p>Reinstall the side panel in the power section of the UPS
cabinet.</p>
         </li>
      </ol>
   </body>
